title: Twin suicide blasts rock Afghanistan's capital Kabul
text:
Twin suicide blasts rock Afghanistan's capital Kabul Casualties feared as twin explosions detonate near Afghanistan's parliament offices in Kabul. 10 Jan 2017 12:42 GMT 
Two separate explosions have gone off near the Afghan parliament in the capital, Kabul, according to officials. 
At least one of the blasts on Tuesday was apparently caused by a car bomb, ministry spokesman Sediq Sediqqi told AFP news agency. 
Security sources said casualties were expected, but no exact numbers have yet been released. 
The attack follows a period of relative calm in Kabul.
